      "message": "Do you know how to reference a static method of an anonymous class without going through its constructor? E.g.:\n\n  this.constructor._detailHref(foo)  // From a class method.\n  el.constructor._detailHref(foo)    // From a lit-html template.\n\nI\u0027m happy to apply this change if you don\u0027t mind the more verbose syntax; I just wanted to make sure you\u0027re aware of the trade-off before doing so.\n\nMore on static methods here: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Classes/static.",
